LESSON 3: Mastering CALCULATE() — The Brain of DAX

✅ 1. Basic CALCULATE Syntax
CALCULATE(
    <expression>,
    <filters>
)


Example:

Sales_India =
CALCULATE(
    SUM(Sales[Amount]),
    Sales[Country] = "India"
)

✅ 2. CALCULATE is the ONLY function that can change filter context

CALCULATE can:

✔ Apply a filter
Sales_2023 =
CALCULATE( SUM(Sales[Amount]), Sales[Year] = 2023 )

✔ Remove a filter
Sales_All_Products =
CALCULATE( SUM(Sales[Amount]), ALL(Sales[Product]) )

✔ Replace a filter
Sales_Only_A =
CALCULATE( SUM(Sales[Amount]), Product[Name] = "A" )

✔ Add multiple filters
Sales_India_2023 =
CALCULATE(
    SUM(Sales[Amount]),
    Sales[Country] = "India",
    Sales[Year] = 2023
)

⭐ VERY IMPORTANT:
CALCULATE + ALL

Used to remove filters and compute totals/percentages.

Total Sales (Ignore Filters) =
CALCULATE(
    SUM(Sales[Amount]),
    ALL(Sales)
)

⭐ CALCULATE + FILTER

Used for advanced logics.

High Value Customers =
CALCULATE(
    SUM(Sales[Amount]),
    FILTER(Sales, Sales[Amount] > 5000)
)

⭐ CALCULATE + VALUES

Used for dynamic comparisons.

Example: Sales for selected product’s category.
